===subject:Reply to Kathryn
===from:Robert Napier
===date:Mon Apr 14  9:55:29 2003
===message:Kathryn, I do think that it is un-American not to respect your President, because we establish a system for electing our President and if we don’t like the system then we have the right to change it. We have told the world and ourselves that the President is a leader and what kind of message does it tell everyone else if we our unable to come together in supporting him.  There is always a difference between respect and rudeness. We will always have the right to speak against someone in this country, but when we do the delivery the message it should be one of thought and insight and not one of disrespect. One example is, the type forum that we use in this class. Anyone could response to your message saying a number a rude remarks about your message, but I have found that people respond in a positive way. There actions show, that they respect what I have to say in the forum whether they agree with my viewpoints and this is the type of respect that I am talking about.  
=========yorg=========
